summary: "Evil’s plans always contain the seeds of its own undoing, no matter how clever they seem at the time,” Aziraphale tells...
body:
“Evil’s plans always contain the seeds of its own undoing, no matter how clever they seem at the time,” Aziraphale tells Crowley, who Aziraphale has watched spend the last several hundred years making life worse for people around London in particular without ever once considering he lives in London before doing it.

“For my money, it was just a regular cock-up,” Crowley replies, well aware of the implications and deliberately ignoring them as he most likely has for several hundred years at this point.

summary: Crowley lifted his glass of champagne in a toast. “To the world.”  Azirapahel raised his own glass in kind, an expression of...
body:
Crowley lifted his glass of champagne in a toast. “To the world.”

Azirapahel raised his own glass in kind, an expression of tender adoration on his face as he repeated, “To the world.”

And yes, he meant The World, with its several billion humans, and beasts and creatures of the land, sea, and air. And yes, he meant the beauty of creation as it stood. But he also meant his own little world. The bookshop, and tea, and wine, and the excellent meal he was about to share…and the one he would share it with.

He was content, and full to bursting with love. And for the first time he felt no trepidation at letting it show as he smiled at Crowley before they drank their champagne.
